The overall performance ratings are categorized as: 
- 'Outstanding Player' if a player scored at least one goal and has no disciplinary counts; 
- 'Needs Improvement' if a player scored no goals and has at least one disciplinary count; 
- 'Average Performance' otherwise.

- seasons can be considered as 'seasons' of a sports league; 
- the performance rating can be viewed as an evaluation of a player's skills and actions in the match; 
- a match can be considered as an event in the season where two teams compete.
